The paper proposes a novel policy design for reinforcement learning agents that operate in complex environments. The paper focuses on the design of the policy and does not involve any specific application domain. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to the design and analysis of algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data. The paper also involves the use of information-theoretic mechanisms, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well. The paper also involves the use of reinforcement learning, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves the use of ensembles of primitives, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.MA (Multiagent Systems).
